TextBody:
Hello Alan A.,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support. My name is Josh, and I'm happy to help. Just to make sure I'm understanding your issue, Netwrix Enterprise Auditor's Window's solution is still reporting disabled admin accounts as active, and the latest scan on those servers is reportedly from 03/19.

The Windows solution is comprised of a number of smaller collectors that gather different components of targeted Windows Servers. It sounds like one or more of those scans is failing to run regularly.

I'd think it's best to review over a remote session. Please use the following link to schedule at your convenience:

https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=eJ9JK02h9R9ThbTflrHwbaTU77fmUz.EZwXWVQH_mQk-Z&MeetingID=a8EK3r8JbqHkfus2vSEGbRiuJImLhopFQcPppbxTKlc-Z

Thank you,

Joshua Sexton

TextBody:
Hello Alan A.,

Thank you for meeting with me today. In our session we investigated Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA)'s Local Admins scan job and report. We found that users who have been removed from the local admin groups are still showing in the reports. The database tables correctly indicate that the users haven't been reporting in that group for some time but are not automatically removing the users from the group.

Like we discussed, I'm going to do some research and test on this. I will let you know as soon as I have next steps. Thank you for your patience.

Thank you,
